ξ 103. No valid stipulation can be made to convey to a person who has not power over the stipulator, whence the question has been mooted to what extent a stipulation for payment to the stipulator and a stranger is valid. My school hold that it is valid for the whole sum sti pulated, and that the stipulator is entitled to the whole, just as if the sti-anger had not been men- tioned. The other school hold that he is only entitled to the moiety.

ξ 104. No valid stipulation can · be made between a person under power and the person to whom he is subject. A slave and a person in mancipation can incur an obligation neither to the person in whose power or mancipation they are, nor to any other person.
